			  <section>
			    <h3>The RITMARE Suite Software: Objectives</h3>
			    <p><strong>Bottom-up strategy: enable researchers to autonomously contribute to the infrastructure</strong></p>
			    <ul>
			      <li>enablement of independent nodes of geo-data provision (inside and outside RITMARE): 
				<ul>
				  <li> maps/layers </li>
				  <li> observations </li>
				</ul>
			      </li>
			    </ul>
			    <ul>
			      <li>semantics-enriched (and -assisted) MD creation: 
				<ul>
				  <li> fine-grained Metadata (data-sets, sensors) </li>
				  <li> leveraging controlled vocabularies and RDF-based data structures (FOAF description of the project’s researcher, organisation, ). </li>
				</ul>
			      </li>
			    </ul>
			  </section>

			  <section>
			    <h3>Software Components (FLOSS)</h3>
			    <ul>
			      <li>GeoNode 2.0</li>
			      <ul>
				<li>GeoServer 2.4</li>
				<li>PyCSW</li>
				<li>Django web framework</li>
				<li>PostgreSQL/PostGIS</li>
			      </ul>
			      <li>SOS 52°North 4.0.0</li>
			      <ul>
				<li>Embedded EDI Metadata </li>
			      </ul>
			      <li>RITMARE Software Suite (formerly StarterKit)</li>
			    </ul>
			  </section>

			  <section>
			    <h3>RITMARE Software Suite: additional components</h3>
			    <ul>
			      <li><strong>SOS Manager</strong> Supports editing of SensorML for
							      registering a new sensor and allows upload of observations
							      as tabular data in a text file.
							      
			      <li><strong>SOS Client</strong> The interface allows to easily interact
				with an SOS to retrieve, for each sensor,
				position, parameter list, offerings, and values.
			      <li><strong>EDI Client</strong> The client-side component of the customizable,
				semantics-aware metadata editing service.
			    </ul>
			  </section>

			  <section>			 
